The Gauteng Provincial Government Command Council gives an update on the 21-day nationwide lockdown and additional measures put in place to curb the spread of COVID-19. The Provincial Executive Council outlines measures to be taken in the coming week, where vulnerable groups will be collecting social grants across the province. In the public interest none of our coronavirus news coverage will be behind our paywall, it is available free for all to read. If you would like to support our mission of delivering award-winning, independent local news, please consider taking out a subscription by clicking here: www.dispatchLIVE.co.za/buy/.